# Yemen Flow Hub — Root Rules

Read `AGENTS.md` at the root before taking any action. It is the single file of truth.

## This Repo Scope
- Tracks: `docs/`, `DESIGN.md`, `AI-ENGINEERING-PROMPT.md`, `AGENTS.md`, root configs
- Does NOT contain runnable app code
- `lovable/` is a read-only reference prototype — never modify it

## Git
Root monorepo remote: `git@github.com:majedsiefalnasr/yemen-flow-hub.git`
Tracks everything: docs, backend, frontend.

- Docs/root changes → commit from root only
- Backend changes → commit from `backend/` (team repo) then from root (monorepo)
- Frontend changes → commit from `frontend/` (team repo) then from root (monorepo)
- Commit format: `type(scope): description`

## Docs Are Law
Documentation in `docs/` overrides all AI assumptions.
If a library doc conflicts with `docs/`, the project docs win.

## Context7
Always fetch current library docs via:
```bash
npx ctx7@latest library "<name>" "<question>"
npx ctx7@latest docs <id> "<question>"
```
